<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="5bede8d7-8bd5-567a-a2c4-06f99db70fee" activityNameId="0ebf588c-6dac-4d6d-b841-9e2be582e905" parentActivityId="31f142fb-4352-4a50-afd7-1d5cabc9c9f4" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of leachate, SLF, waste emulsion paint, wastewater treatment</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the leachate being available at the gate of the wastewater treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the leachate to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the wastewater being treated and waste-specific emissions released to the environment. Expenditures from treatment of wastewater in waste treatment plant are included as well as relevant infrastructure of the plant. Emissions from any sludge digestion, biogas generation and utilization (heeding specific wastewater composition) are also included. Waste-specific direct emissions of untreated wastewater and required territory-specific infrastructure for sewers are not contained within this dataset but instead in the regional market datasets for this wastewater.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the treatment of a wastewater (leachate), that is exclusively generated in another waste treatment. It models the purification in wastewater treatment (WWT) a leachate, generated during the sanitary landfilling (SLF) of 'waste emulsion paint'. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for 'waste emulsion paint'. The wastewater has a content of TOC: 0.03059 kg/m3, 0.03059 and COD: 0.11926 kg/m3. TOC is equal to C present in the wastewater, COD is calculated as TOC/0.2565 and BOD is calculated as COD/0.53034. Detailed elemental composition can be found in the properties of the wastewater treated. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 0%.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="a84d0ee4-d77c-4905-b876-3ef60873c763">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3700:Sewerage</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="f9221622-cc45-11de-98ed-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">Europe without Switzerland</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The site has mean annual temperature (MAT) of 10.403 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 960.474141305017 mm/year, mean annual actual evaporation (EAT) of 450.073365823956 mm/year. In the WWT plant, 0.0182% of its water input are lost due to evaporation from pools, 0.00161% of water is *gained* from organic mass degradation, and 0.0122% is removed off site via sludge disposal.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">UN data, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&amp;d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a6;</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for the disposal of a selected wastewater in Europe without Switzerland. The reference unit is 1 m3 wastewater input. This activity represents the treatment of a specific wastewater in a WWT plant (while direct emissions and sewering are heeded in the upstream market dataset for this wastewater). The size of the treatment plant infrastructure is for a supranational region average territory situation. The assumed size of the WWTP treats 99.2 Mio m3 per year. The mixture of WWTP with one, two, or three stages is 1.89%-22.8%-75.3%. The actual, waste-specific oxygen requirement in the 0.0288681649752562 kg O. The digestion process produces 17.6171878525575 litres of biogas with an energy content of 0.393403924335694MJ. 74.6% of the biogas is utilized for energy. The remainder is flared. The gross electric efficiency is 0%. The gross thermal efficiency is 0%. After digestion, the remaining total sludge mass (dry matter) is 0.1371kg DM.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2010-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
